species_richness_table1 <- merged_fD_SR %>%  
  group_by(GRIDID,GRID_LON, GRID_LAT, ABBR) %>%
  summarise(species_count1 = n_distinct(COMMON_NAME)) %>%
  filter(!ABBR %in% c("AK", "HI")) %>%
  filter(GRID_LON <= 125) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  distinct(GRIDID, .keep_all = TRUE)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'GRIDID', 'GRID_LON', 'GRID_LAT'. You can
## override using the `.groups` argument.
nrow(species_richness_table1)
## [1] 7425
columns_to_classify <- c("WOOD_SPGR_GREENVOL_DRYWT", "ShadeTol", "DroughtTol", "FloodTol", "StdValue")
for (col in columns_to_classify) {
  breaks <- seq(min(merged_fD_SR[[col]]), max(merged_fD_SR[[col]]), length.out = 6)
  merged_fD_SR[[paste0(col, "_Class")]] <- cut(merged_fD_SR[[col]], breaks = breaks, labels = FALSE)
}
result <- merged_fD_SR %>%
  group_by(GRIDID, GRID_LAT, GRID_LON, ABBR, COMMON_NAME) %>%
  summarise(
    ShadeTol_count = n_distinct(ShadeTol_Class, na.rm = TRUE),
    DroughtTol_count = n_distinct(DroughtTol_Class, na.rm = TRUE),
    FloodTol_count = n_distinct(FloodTol_Class, na.rm = TRUE),
    Height_count = n_distinct(StdValue_Class, na.rm = TRUE),
    WOOD_SPGR_GREENVOL_DRYWT_count = n_distinct(WOOD_SPGR_GREENVOL_DRYWT_Class, na.rm = TRUE)
  )
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'GRIDID', 'GRID_LAT', 'GRID_LON', 'ABBR'.
## You can override using the `.groups` argument.
print(result)
## # A tibble: 93,145  10

diversity_result <- result %>% 
filter(!ABBR %in% c("AK", "HI")) %>%
  filter(GRID_LON <= 125)
Total_Diversity_count <- diversity_result %>%
  mutate(TotalDiversity = ShadeTol_count + DroughtTol_count + FloodTol_count + Height_count + WOOD_SPGR_GREENVOL_DRYWT_count) 
print(Total_Diversity_count)

# Convert species richness to a factor for discrete coloring
species_richness$species_count1 <- as.factor(species_richness$species_count1)
# Convert species_count to numeric
species_richness$species_count1 <- as.numeric(as.character(species_richness$species_count1))

# Now try the plot again
ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = states_sf_filter, fill = "transparent", color = "black") +
  geom_point(data = species_richness, aes(x = GRID_LON, y = GRID_LAT, color = species_count1), size = 1.4) +
  scale_color_viridis_c(option = "plasma",limits = c(0, 30),  # Set the range for the color scale
    breaks = seq(4, 25, by = 3)) +

  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Species Richness by GRIDID")

ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = states_sf_filter, fill = "transparent", color = "black") +

Standardizing Species Richness

species_richness$species_count1_rescaled <- (species_richness$species_count1 - min_value) / (max_value1 - min_value)
min(species_richness$species_count1_rescaled) 
## [1] 0
max(species_richness$species_count1_rescaled) 
## [1] 1
scale_limits <- c(0, 1)
ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = states_sf_filter, fill = "transparent", color = "black") +
  geom_point(data = species_richness, aes(x = GRID_LON, y = GRID_LAT, color = species_count1_rescaled), size = 1) +
  scale_color_viridis_c(option = "turbo", name = "Species Richness Scale", limits = scale_limits) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Standardized Species Richness")

Standardizing Functional Group DIversity

species_richness$TotalDiversity_rescaled <- (species_richness$TotalDiversity - min_value2) / (max_value2 - min_value2)
min(species_richness$TotalDiversity_rescaled) 
## [1] 0
max(species_richness$TotalDiversity_rescaled) 
## [1] 1
scale_limits <- c(0, 1)
ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = states_sf_filter, fill = "transparent", color = "black") +
  geom_point(data = species_richness, aes(x = GRID_LON, y = GRID_LAT, color = TotalDiversity_rescaled), size = 1) +
  scale_color_viridis_c(option = "turbo", name = "Total Diversity Scale", limits = scale_limits) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Standardize Total Functional Group Diversity") 

# Combine the rescaled data into a single dataframe
combined_data <- data.frame(
  species_richness = species_richness$species_count1_rescaled,
  functional_diversity = species_richness$TotalDiversity_rescaled,
  GRID_LAT = species_richness$GRID_LAT,
  GRID_LON = species_richness$GRID_LON
  
)

# Calculate the difference
combined_data$difference <- combined_data$species_richness - combined_data$functional_diversity

min(combined_data$difference)
## [1] -0.5812808
max(combined_data$difference)
## [1] 0.01313629
# Standardize the difference (z-score)
combined_data$difference_z <- scale(combined_data$difference)

# Verify the results
colnames(combined_data)

## [4] "GRID_LON"             "difference"           "difference_z"
print(head(combined_data$difference))
## [1] -0.04761905 -0.04761905 -0.04761905 -0.04761905 -0.15599343 -0.04761905
combined_data$difference_z <- scale(combined_data$difference)
combined_data$classification <- cut(combined_data$difference_z,
                                    breaks = c(-Inf, -1, 1, Inf),
                                    labels = c("LSR_HFD", "Balanced", "HSR_LFD"),
                                    include.lowest = TRUE)


library(tmap)
## Warning: package 'tmap' was built under R version 4.3.3
## The legacy packages maptools, rgdal, and rgeos, underpinning the sp package,
## which was just loaded, will retire in October 2023.
## Please refer to R-spatial evolution reports for details, especially
## https://r-spatial.org/r/2023/05/15/evolution4.html.
## It may be desirable to make the sf package available;
## package maintainers should consider adding sf to Suggests:.
## The sp package is now running under evolution status 2
##      (status 2 uses the sf package in place of rgdal)
## Breaking News: tmap 3.x is retiring. Please test v4, e.g. with
## remotes::install_github('r-tmap/tmap')
# Define quantiles for classification
quantiles <- quantile(combined_data$difference, probs = c(0.25, 0.75))

# Classify based on quantiles
combined_data$classification <- cut(combined_data$difference,
                                    breaks = c(-Inf, quantiles[1], quantiles[2], Inf),
                                    labels = c("LSR_HFD", "Balanced", "HSR_LFD"),
                                    include.lowest = TRUE)

gdf <- st_as_sf(combined_data, coords = c("GRID_LON", "GRID_LAT"), crs = 4326)

# Combine with spatial data
gdf$classification <- combined_data$classification
gdf$difference <- combined_data$difference
palette <- c("LSR_HFD" = "red", "Balanced" = "grey", "HSR_LFD" = "blue")


gdf$classification <- factor(gdf$classification, 
                             levels = c("LSR_HFD", "Balanced", "HSR_LFD"))


tm_shape(states_sf_filter) +
  tm_borders(col = "black") +  # Add state boundaries
  tm_shape(gdf) +
  tm_dots(col = "classification", 
          palette = palette, 
          size = 0.07, 
          title = "Classifications") +
  tm_layout(title = "Areas Classified by Species Richness and Functional Diversity",
            legend.outside = TRUE)

gdf <- st_as_sf(species_richness, coords = c("GRID_LON", "GRID_LAT"), crs = 4326)
coords <- st_coordinates(gdf)
nb <- knn2nb(knearneigh(coords, k = 4))
listw <- nb2listw(nb, style = "W")
# Calculate Global Moran's I
global_moran <- moran.test(species_richness$species_count1, listw)

# Extract Global Moran's I statistic and p-value
global_moran_I <- global_moran$estimate[["Moran I statistic"]]
global_moran_pvalue <- global_moran$p.value

print(paste("Global Moran's I:", round(global_moran_I, 3)))
## [1] "Global Moran's I: 0.711"
print(paste("p-value:", round(global_moran_pvalue, 3)))
## [1] "p-value: 0"

Hotspot and coldspot analysis for TSR

species_richness <- st_as_sf(species_richness, coords = c("GRID_LON", "GRID_LAT"), crs = 4326)
y <- species_richness$species_count1  

# Create a spatial weights matrix
coords <- st_coordinates(species_richness)
knn <- knearneigh(coords, k = 5)  
nb <- knn2nb(knn)
w <- nb2listw(nb, style = "W")
gi_star <- localG(y, w)
species_richness$gi_star <- gi_star
species_richness$z_score <- scale(gi_star)

species_richness$hotspot_type <- cut(species_richness$gi_star, 
                                     breaks = c(-Inf, -1.96, -1.65, 1.65, 1.96, Inf),
                                     labels = c( 
                                                "Cold Spot - 95% Confidence", 
                                                "Cold Spot - 90% Confidence",
                                                "Not Significant",
                                                "Hot Spot - 90% Confidence",
                                                "Hot Spot - 95% Confidence"
                                                ))


library(RColorBrewer)
library(ggplot2)
ggplot(species_richness) +
  geom_sf(aes(color = hotspot_type)) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Cold Spot - 95% Confidence" = "blue",
                                "Cold Spot - 90% Confidence" = "light blue",
                                "Not Significant" = "grey",
                                "Hot Spot - 90% Confidence" = "yellow",
                                "Hot Spot - 95% Confidence" = "red")) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Hotspots and Coldspots of Species Richness",
       color = "Significance Level")

Spatial Autocorrelation Analysis for Functional Group Diversity

# 1. Prepare the data
y_total <- species_richness$TotalDiversity

# 2. Create spatial weights matrix
coords_total <- st_coordinates(species_richness)
knn_total <- knearneigh(coords_total, k = 5)  # You can adjust k if needed
nb_total <- knn2nb(knn_total)
w_total <- nb2listw(nb_total, style = "W")

# 3. Perform global Moran's I test
moran_result_total <- moran.test(y_total, w_total)
print(moran_result_total)
## 
##  Moran I test under randomisation
## 
## data:  y_total  
## weights: w_total    
## 
## Moran I statistic standard deviate = 90.094, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: greater
## sample estimates:
## Moran I statistic       Expectation          Variance 
##      6.294873e-01     -1.346983e-04      4.883923e-05

Hotspot and Coldspot analysis for FD

# Calculate Getis-Ord Gi* statistic
gi_star_total <- localG(y_total, w_total)

# Add the Gi* statistic to your dataframe and classify hotspots/coldspots
species_richness$gi_star_total <- gi_star_total
species_richness$hotspot_type_total <- cut(species_richness$gi_star_total, 
                                     breaks = c(-Inf, -1.96, -1.65, 1.65, 1.96, Inf),
                                     labels = c("Cold Spot - 95% Confidence", 
                                                "Cold Spot - 90% Confidence",
                                                "Not Significant",
                                                "Hot Spot - 90% Confidence",
                                                "Hot Spot - 95% Confidence"))

# Visualize the results
ggplot(species_richness) +
  geom_sf(aes(color = hotspot_type_total), size = 3) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Cold Spot - 95% Confidence" = "blue",
                                "Cold Spot - 90% Confidence" = "light blue",
                                "Not Significant" = "grey",
                                "Hot Spot - 90% Confidence" = "yellow",
                                "Hot Spot - 95% Confidence" = "red")) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Hotspots and Coldspots of Functional Diversity",
       color = "Significance Level")

library(sf)
library(dplyr)

  group_by(LKEY) %>%
  summarise() %>%

remaining_duplicates <- sapolygon_grouped %>%
  group_by(LKEY) %>%
  filter(n() > 1) %>%
  ungroup()

if(nrow(remaining_duplicates) == 0) {
  print("LKEYs are unique.")
} else {
  print("remaining some duplicate LKEYs.")
  print(remaining_duplicates)
}

#Function to read the layer from gNATSGO soil data
read_gnatsgo_layer <- function(gnatso_data, layer_name) {
  st_read(gnatso_data, layer = layer_name)
}

soil_data <- mapunit %>%
  left_join(component, by = "mukey") %>%
  left_join(chorizon, by = "cokey") %>%
  group_by(lkey) %>%
  summarise(
    om = mean(c(om_l, om_r), na.rm = TRUE),
    ph1to1h2o = mean(c(ph1to1h2o_l, ph1to1h2o_r, ph1to1h2o_h), na.rm = TRUE),
    ph01mcacl2 = mean(c(ph01mcacl2_l, ph01mcacl2_r, ph01mcacl2_h), na.rm = TRUE),
    sandvc = mean(c(sandvc_l, sandvc_r, sandvc_h), na.rm = TRUE),
    sandco = mean(c(sandco_l, sandco_r, sandco_h), na.rm = TRUE),
    sandmed = mean(c(sandmed_l, sandmed_r, sandmed_h), na.rm = TRUE),
    sandfine = mean(c(sandfine_l, sandfine_r, sandfine_h), na.rm = TRUE),
    sandvf = mean(c(sandvf_l, sandvf_r, sandvf_h), na.rm = TRUE),
    silttotal = mean(c(silttotal_l, silttotal_r, silttotal_h), na.rm = TRUE),
    siltco = mean(c(siltco_l, siltco_r, siltco_h), na.rm = TRUE),
    siltfine = mean(c(siltfine_l, siltfine_r, siltfine_h), na.rm = TRUE),
    claytotal = mean(c(claytotal_l, claytotal_r, claytotal_h), na.rm = TRUE),
    claysizedcarb = mean(c(claysizedcarb_l, claysizedcarb_r, claysizedcarb_h), na.rm = TRUE),
    cec7 = mean(c(cec7_l, cec7_r, cec7_h), na.rm = TRUE)
  ) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  dplyr::select(lkey, everything())


# Remove rows with NA values
soil_data <- na.omit(soil_data)
print(soil_data)

# Join soil attributes back to unique LKEYs
sapolygon_joined <- left_join(sapolygon_grouped_df, soil_data, by = c("LKEY" = "lkey"))

# Check the number of rows in the joined data
print(nrow(sapolygon_joined))   #3817
## [1] 3187
# Join LKEY with geometries
final_df <- left_join(sapolygon_df, sapolygon_joined, by = "LKEY")

# Check if the row count matches the original
final_nrow <- nrow(final_df)
final_nrow   #16592
## [1] 16592
print(final_nrow == original_nrow)  # true
## [1] TRUE
sf_object <- st_as_sf(final_df)
class(sf_object)
## [1] "sf"         "data.frame"
# soil attributes
attributes <- c("om", "ph1to1h2o", "ph01mcacl2", "sandvc", "sandco", 
                "sandmed", "sandfine", "sandvf", "silttotal", "siltco", 
                "siltfine", "claytotal", "claysizedcarb", "cec7")

# Create an empty raster with 20km x 20km 
raster_template <- raster(extent(sf_object), resolution = c(20000, 20000))

# Function to rasterize each attribute
rasterize_attribute <- function(attribute) {
  rasterize(sf_object, raster_template, field = attribute)
}

# Rasterize each attribute and store in a list
rasters <- lapply(attributes, rasterize_attribute)
names(rasters) <- attributes
FD_SR <- read.csv("richness_fdiversity.csv")
nrow(FD_SR)
## [1] 7425
# Convert FD_SR to an sf object 
FD_SR_sf <- st_as_sf(FD_SR, coords = c("GRID_LON", "GRID_LAT"), crs = 4326)
FD_SR_sf <- st_transform(FD_SR_sf, st_crs(sf_object))
print(st_crs(FD_SR_sf))
